Market Segmentation: 
Personal protective equipment market is segmented of the basis of product type and end- use industry. The growth amongst the different segments helps you in attaining the knowledge related to the different growth factors expected to be prevalent throughout the market and formulate different strategies to help identify core application areas and the difference in your target markets.
On the basis of product type, personal protective equipment market is segmented into hands & arm protection equipment, protective clothing, foot & leg protection equipment, respiratory protection equipment, eye & face protection equipment, head protection equipment other personal protective equipment, and hearing protection. Hands & arm protection equipment is further sub segmented into protective gloves, wrist cuffs and armlets, elbow protectors and others.  Protective gloves are further bifurcated into disposable gloves, leather gloves, and others. Others are further bifurcated into mitts, barrier creams. Protective clothing is ahead sub segmented into full body suits, surgical gowns, and others. Others are fragmented into coveralls, and safety vest. Foot & leg protection equipment is additionally divided into Safety boots and shoes, leggings, and others. Others are ahead fragmented into metatarsal guards, and toe guards. Respiratory protection equipment is further bifurcated into respirators and breathing apparatus. Eye & face protection equipment is ahead sub segmented into safety spectacles, welding shields and others. Others are further segmented into safety goggles and face shield. Head protection equipment is further fragmented into hard hats and others. Fall protection is ahead divided into full body harness and others. Hearing protection is fragmented into earplugs and others.
The end use segment for personal protective equipment market includes construction, manufacturing, chemicals, oil and gas, food, pharmaceuticals, transportation, mining, firefighting and others.
